text.paragraph:
Do not start escitalopram tablets in a patient who is being treated with linezolid or intravenous methylene blue because there is an increased risk of serotonin syndrome. In a patient who requires more urgent treatment of a psychiatric condition, other interventions, including hospitalization, should be considered [see Contraindications (
                              4.1

                           )].

Concomitant use in patients taking pimozide is contraindicated [see Drug Interactions (
                                 7.10


                           )].

